Package org.opends.sdk

OpenDS SDK.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Assertion A compiled attribute value assertion.
AsynchronousConnection An asynchronous connection with a Directory Server over which read and update operations may be performed.
Attribute An attribute, comprising of an attribute description and zero or more attribute values.
Connection A synchronous connection with a Directory Server over which read and update operations may be performed.
ConnectionEventListener An object that registers to be notified when a connection is closed by the application, receives an unsolicited notification, or experiences a fatal error.
ConnectionFactory<C extends AsynchronousConnection> A connection factory provides an interface for obtaining a connection to a Directory Server.
ConnectionFuture<C extends AsynchronousConnection> A handle which can be used to retrieve a requested AsynchronousConnection.
ConnectionResultHandler<C extends AsynchronousConnection,P> A completion handler which is notified when an asynchronous connection attempt has completed.
Entry An entry, comprising of a distinguished name and zero or more attributes.
FilterVisitor<R,P> A visitor of Filters, in the style of the visitor design pattern.
ResultFuture<S extends Result> A handle which can be used to retrieve the Result of an asynchronous Request.
ResultHandler<S extends Result,P> A completion handler for consuming the result of an asynchronous operation.
SearchResultHandler<P> A completion handler for consuming the results of an asynchronous Search operation.
 

Class Summary
AbstractAttribute This class provides a skeletal implementation of the Attribute interface, to minimize the effort required to implement this interface.
AbstractConnectionFactory<C extends AsynchronousConnection> This class provides a skeletal implementation of the ConnectionFactory interface, to minimize the effort required to implement this interface.
AbstractEntry This class provides a skeletal implementation of the Entry interface, to minimize the effort required to implement this interface.
AbstractFilterVisitor<R,P> An abstract filter visitor whose default implementation for all Visitor methods is to invoke AbstractFilterVisitor.visitDefaultFilter(Object).
AttributeDescription An attribute description as defined in RFC 4512 section 2.5.
AuthenticatedConnectionFactory An authenticated connection factory can be used to create pre-authenticated connections to a Directory Server.
AuthenticatedConnectionFactory.AuthenticatedAsynchronousConnection An authenticated asynchronous connection supports all operations except Bind operations.
AuthenticatedConnectionFactory.AuthenticatedConnection An authenticated synchronous connection supports all operations except Bind operations.
Change A modification to be performed on an entry during a Modify operation.
DereferenceAliasesPolicy A Search operation alias dereferencing policy as defined in RFC 4511 section 4.5.1.3 is used to indicate whether or not alias entries (as defined in RFC 4512) are to be dereferenced during stages of a Search operation.
DN A distinguished name (DN).
Filter A search filter as defined in RFC 4511.
LinkedAttribute An implementation of the Attribute interface with predictable iteration order.
Matcher An interface for determining whether entries match a Filter.
ModificationType Created by IntelliJ IDEA.
RDN A relative distinguished name (RDN).
RDN.AttributeTypeAndValue  
ResultCode Defines the set of possible result codes that may be used for providing clients with information about result of processing an operation.
RootDSE Root DSE Entry.
SearchScope This enumeration defines the set of possible scopes that may be used for a search request.
SortedEntry An implementation of the Entry interface which uses a SortedMap for storing attributes.
SynchronousConnection A SynchronousConnection adapts an AsynchronousConnection into a synchronous Connection.
Types This class contains methods for creating and manipulating attributes, entries, and other types of object.
 

Enum Summary
ConditionResult The result of a tri-state logical expression.
 

Exception Summary
DecodeException Thrown when data from an input source cannot be decoded, perhaps due to the data being malformed in some way.
ErrorResultException Thrown when the result code returned in a Result indicates that the Request was unsuccessful.
ErrorResultIOException An ErrorResultIOException adapts an ErrorResultException to an IOException.
InitializationException Thrown to indicate that a connection factory could not be initialized due to a problem with its configuration options.
